"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-patrick-lange-ironman-kona-world-championship-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"German Patrick Lange broke the course record to win a third Ironman Kona World Championship - his first in six years - and become the second-oldest man to win the title.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9633188427514519, \"rank\": 0.031937172939587206, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 14, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\", \"score\": 0.9975417665761573, \"rank\": 0.0024543303627998663, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\"}, {\"begin\": 60, \"end\": 67, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_Triathlon\", \"score\": 0.9999999598317125, \"rank\": 4.0168403764086636e-08, \"text\": \"Ironman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_Triathlon\"}, {\"begin\": 68, \"end\": 72, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9789953866299014, \"rank\": 0.02145526374318022, \"text\": \"Kona\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 73, \"end\": 91, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"score\": 0.9997295072015581, \"rank\": 0.00026277192477936243, \"text\": \"World Championship\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lange, 38, clocked an unofficial 7 hours, 35 minutes, 53 seconds in the 140.6-mile race (2.4-mile swim, 112-mile bike, 26.2-mile run) on Hawaii's Big Island.\", \"from\": 171, \"to\": 328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 308, \"end\": 314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.9999994715609806, \"rank\": 2.632125711594617e-07, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He prevailed by 7:46 over Magnus Ditlev of Denmark.\", \"from\": 329, \"to\": 380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 355, \"end\": 361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magnus_IV_of_Norway\", \"score\": 0.5782991880606438, \"rank\": 0.7094851040452815, \"text\": \"Magnus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magnus_IV_of_Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magnus_IV_of_Norway\"}, {\"begin\": 372, \"end\": 379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 0.9999933712689711, \"rank\": 6.553236318486528e-06, \"text\": \"Denmark\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lange broke the course record of 7:40:24 set by Norwegian Gustav Iden the last time Kona held the men's world championship race in 2022.\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 430, \"end\": 439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.9884420441697249, \"rank\": 0.011135018272609503, \"text\": \"Norwegian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}, {\"begin\": 466, \"end\": 470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9789953866299014, \"rank\": 0.02145526374318022, \"text\": \"Kona\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I always said that my best day is yet to come,\\\" Lange said.\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Nobody believed in me, and this is the day.\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 625, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was the perfect day.\\\"\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's course record has been lowered at the last five editions in Kona dating to 2017.\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 724, \"end\": 728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9789953866299014, \"rank\": 0.02145526374318022, \"text\": \"Kona\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Going into the 2017 race, the course record was 8:03:56.\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 801, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lange was in 13th place after the 112-mile bike, trailing defending champion Sam Laidlow of France by 9:06.\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 910, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Laidlow\", \"score\": 0.999985295493271, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Laidlow\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Laidlow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Laidlow\"}, {\"begin\": 895, \"end\": 901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9702121782145118, \"rank\": 0.028359367493381676, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lange unleashed a 2:37:34 marathon, just off the run course record of 2:36:15 set by Iden in 2022.\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 1010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iden\", \"score\": 0.9999868219146925, \"rank\": 1.2268558106483407e-05, \"text\": \"Iden\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Laidlow shattered his own bike course record of 4:04:36 from 2022 by covering the 112 miles in 3:57:22.\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1115, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Seven total men went faster than the previous bike record.\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Laidlow struggled early on the run and briefly stopped around the 11-mile mark, shortly before Lange passed him.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Laidlow faded all the way to 18th place in 8:02:01, a time that would have been the course record as recently as 2017.\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1412, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He ran his marathon in 3:12:49.\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lange claimed his third Ironman Kona title after winning back to back in 2017 and 2018.\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1533, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1470, \"end\": 1477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_Triathlon\", \"score\": 0.9999999598317125, \"rank\": 4.0168403764086636e-08, \"text\": \"Ironman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_Triathlon\"}, {\"begin\": 1478, \"end\": 1482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9789953866299014, \"rank\": 0.02145526374318022, \"text\": \"Kona\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kona_International_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the second-oldest Ironman men's world champion ever after Australian Craig Alexander, who won the last of his three titles in 2011 at an older 38.\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1558, \"end\": 1565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_Triathlon\", \"score\": 0.9999999598317125, \"rank\": 4.0168403764086636e-08, \"text\": \"Ironman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_Triathlon\"}, {\"begin\": 1598, \"end\": 1608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9784155275282675, \"rank\": 0.020858107819951996, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1615, \"end\": 1624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"score\": 0.9991254000282244, \"rank\": 0.0008670747554553825, \"text\": \"Alexander\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last year, Laidlow became at age 24 the youngest Ironman men's world champion in history, prevailing in Nice, France.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1792, \"end\": 1796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"score\": 0.9999999150823022, \"rank\": 8.491769334131316e-08, \"text\": \"Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\"}, {\"begin\": 1798, \"end\": 1804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9702121782145118, \"rank\": 0.028359367493381676, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Ironman World Championship had been held exclusively in Hawaii from its inception in 1978 through 2019.\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1914, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1811, \"end\": 1837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_World_Championship\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.501467467362684e-23, \"text\": \"Ironman World Championship\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_World_Championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ironman_World_Championship\"}, {\"begin\": 1867, \"end\": 1873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.9999994715609806, \"rank\": 2.632125711594617e-07, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Starting last year, organizers split the men's and women's races with one in Nice and the other on Hawaii's Big Island, alternating years, through 2026.\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 2068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1993, \"end\": 1997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"score\": 0.9999999150823022, \"rank\": 8.491769334131316e-08, \"text\": \"Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\"}, {\"begin\": 2015, \"end\": 2021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.9999994715609806, \"rank\": 2.632125711594617e-07, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That change was made so that the two fields can \\\"have a focused\\\" race experience.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Sept. 22, German Laura Philipp won the Ironman women's world championship in Nice.\", \"from\": 2153, \"to\": 2238, \"entities\": [{